{
  "texts": [
    "The genome sequence of EDT was annotated with RNA sequencing data from different tissues, resulting in a total of 36,229 proteincoding genes (Additional file 1: Table S18).",
    "The assembled genome of EDT exhibited strong collinearity with the genetic map constructed de novo from the RIL population data and the previously assembled genomes (V2 and HERA versions; Additional file 2: Fig.",
    "S21), demonstrating the reliability of the assembled genome.Utilizing the high-quality genome assembly of EDT, pairwise genome alignment was conducted with Pinku1, a difficult-to-dehull type (DDT) from the NL group.",
    "A total of 344,323 SNPs and 99,617 indels (<50 bp) were detected in this comparison (Additional file 1: Table S20).",
    "Among these variants, 1.76% are nonsynonymous, potentially affecting gene function."
  ]
}